05048nam a22008295i 9789048551767DE-B159720230529101353.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||230529t20232023ne     fo  d z      eng d  a97890485517677 a10.1515/97890485517672doi  a(DE-B1597)650942  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anecNL 4aNA1116b.N58 2023 7aARC0050502bisacsh04a720.94509033223/eng/202305011 aNixon, Martin, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aArchitecture, Opportunity, and Conflict in Eighteenth-Century Sicily :bRebuilding after Natural Disaster /cMartin Nixon. 1aAmsterdam : bAmsterdam University Press, c[2023] 4c©2023  a1 online resource (284 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aVisual and Material Culture, 1300 –1700 ;v4600tFrontmatter -- tTable of Contents -- tList of illustrations -- tAcknowledgments -- tIntroduction -- t1. Sicily as a Colonial Possession c. 1600– 1750: Subordination and Resistance -- t2. The Hexagonal Towns of Avola and Grammichele: Urbanism, Fortification, and Coercion -- t3. The Palaces of Noto: Ornament, Order, and Opportunism -- t4. The Palazzo Biscari in Catania: Lightness, Refinement, and Distinction -- t5. The Palazzo Beneventano in Scicli: Trauma and Violence -- t6. The Palaces of Ragusa: Abundance, Famine, and the Grotesque -- tConclusion -- tGlossary -- tBibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe catastrophic Sicilian earthquake of 1693 led to the rebuilding of over 60 towns in the island’s south-west. The rebuilding extended into the eighteenth century and gave opportunities for the reassertion and the transformation of power relations. Although eight of the towns are now protected by UNESCO, the remarkable architecture resulting from this rebuilding is little known outside Sicily. This is the first book-length study in English of this interesting area of early modern architecture. Rather than seek to address all of the towns, five case studies discuss key aspects of the rebuilding by approaching the architecture from different scales, from that of a whole town to parts of a town, or single buildings, or parts of buildings and their decoration. Each case study also investigates a different theoretical assumption in architecture, including ideas of the Baroque, rational planning, and the relegation of decoration in architectural discourse.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aArchitecturezItalyzSicilyy18th century. 4aArt and Material Culture. 4aEarly Modern Studies. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 7aARCHITECTURE / History / Baroque & Rococo.2bisacsh  aEarly Modern, Sicily, Architecture and Power, Urbanism, Baroque.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2023z9783111318097oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2023 Englishz978311131903208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG0 cprintz978946372573640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048551767?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048551767423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048551767/original  a978-3-11-102374-8  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131903-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_AD  aEBA_EE